\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 16. A. tetraphylla} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 719 (1753) ({\i Physanthyllis tetraphylla} (L.) Boiss.). Procumbent annual. Stems villous to hirsute. Leaves imparipinnate, with (1-)5 leaflets, the large, more or less obovate terminal leaflet much exceeding the small, lateral leaflets, hairy on both surfaces, much less above. Flowers in axillary fascicles of 1-7. Calyx 12-15 × 4·5-6 mm, inflated at anthesis, later up to 12 mm wide, gibbous, especially so in fruit, densely sericeous, frequently reddish near the apex, the teeth subequal, the mouth of the calyx straight. Corolla yellow, the keel often red at apex. Legume usually 2-seeded, constricted between the seeds.{\i  Mediterranean region, S. Portugal.} Al Bl Co Cr Ga Gr Hs It Ju Lu Sa Si.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 17. A. lotoides} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 720 (1753) ({\i Cornicina lotoides} (L.) Boiss.). Erect annual. Stems villous to hirsute. Lowermost leaves often reduced to the terminal leaflet, the upper irregularly imparipinnate with (3-)5-7 subequal, narrowly lanceolate to oblanceolate leaflets, hairy above and beneath, strongly so on the margin. Heads 4- to 8-flowered, subtended by digitate bracts borne just beneath the flowers. Calyx 9-11 mm, tubular, with 5 unequal triangular teeth and an oblique mouth, long pubescent. Corolla yellow to orange. Legume straight, 6- to 10-seeded, erect, the infructescence forming a compact long narrow head. {\i Spain and Portugal.} Hs Lu.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 18. A. cornicina} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 719 (1753) ({\i Cornicina loeflingii} Boiss.). Annual. Stems ascending to erect, villous to hirsute. Lowermost leaves reduced to the terminal leaflet, the upper with up to 9 subequal, very narrowly elliptical leaflets, sericeous above and beneath. Heads 9- or more-flowered, subtended by digitate bracts. Calyx 5-7 mm, not inflated or gibbous at anthesis but inflated in fruit, with 5 unequal teeth and an oblique mouth. Corolla yellow-orange. Legume winged, curved into an almost complete circle, completely included within the calyx. Seeds 3 or more.{\i  C. & S. Spain, Portugal. }Hs Lu.
